<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>Voluntary PvP is the concept here - VOLUNTARY</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?TheBlack[BCK]">TheBlack[BCK]</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 3:46 p.m. 9/2/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Voluntary PvP is the concept here - VOLUNTARY<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=363" TARGET=_self>This is true and leads to a good idea on Zone importance...(TXT read)</A> (Kellindel)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>

<BR>Such a system would only work if you introduce a second PvP switch, I like to call the Role Playing PvP Switch (RP PvP).
<BR>Anyone who flips it would be saying they agree to fight under the faction rules. Any system that attempts to go around this important concept of voluntary PvP is going to get the AXE.
<P>You still have the same issues of balance when you have a 50th Troll bashing 1-4 humans in the bat yards outside Quenyons. Forget it. 989 is not that dumb and they are not going to do such a thing. Faction hits with the level limits in place is fine, PvP between those who have flipped the switch is fine. Personally I don't think the faction system is needed for PvP, but I can live with it if 989 enforfces it or if they add a second RP PVP switch. Either way I still think we need level limits, and there is no getting around the PvP flag.
<P>&gt; Its obvious with such a diverse game like EQ... there should be
<BR>&gt; racial hatred in the game.
<BR>&gt; Whatever the reason is...
<BR>&gt; For instance.. a wood elf ranger should be able to kill Ogres
<BR>&gt; and Trolls and maybe even Dark elves with out any restrctions.
<BR>&gt; In this case the ranger would have to travel into the Ogre and
<BR>&gt; Troll territory to accomplish such feats.. and when there he
<BR>&gt; will be at a disadvantage and can get jumped by numerous npcs as
<BR>&gt; well as PCs.
<BR>&gt; This wil make a great roleplaying side of EQ... and thus giving
<BR>&gt; Zones and areas of the map some importance and influence on
<BR>&gt; where u travel...
<BR>&gt; Likewise.. if an Ogre thinks he can go to Fadywar and bash some
<BR>&gt; heads in... he could do that by hunting the roads and forests
<BR>&gt; for would be easy kills... tho could run into a band of elves or
<BR>&gt; whatever and get serously jacked up.
<BR>&gt; I can see this situatuion easily.. a PC Ogre Warrior is
<BR>&gt; terroszing the inhabitants of Fadywar and its up to some of the
<BR>&gt; locals to beat them down.. and kick thier sorry hides off their
<BR>&gt; land.
<BR>
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
